The paper deals with distributed algorithms for computing shortest paths on networks, which is a topic that falls under the area of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from network information theory (cs.NI) and approximation algorithms (cs.AL). Additionally, the paper mentions ruling sets (cs.GT), which are a well-known tool in graph algorithms.
